    "en": {
      "title": "India's new president is a tribal woman",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "He has secured more than 50 percent of the total vote value after three rounds of counting.",
        "India has elected its second woman and first tribal woman president.",
        "After this, the swearing-in ceremony of the new president will be held on July 25.",
        "In this situation, Draupadi Murmu, a famous tribal leader from Odisha and former governor of Jharkhand state, contested as the candidate of the National Democratic Alliance led by the ruling Bharatiya Janata Party.",
        "Yashwant Sinha, a former Union minister and member of the Trinamool Congress, contested as the general candidate of the opposition parties. (a)"
      ],
